<HEADLINE>
NATIONAL YOUTH COMMISSION RECRUITS YOUTH TRAVEL VOLUNTEERS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  April 3 (CNA) 04/03/07  20:35:35 (By Y.L. Kao)
</P>
<P>
In an effort to promote youth tourism in Taiwan, the National
Youth Commission (NYC) is recruiting 120 youth travel volunteers
aged between 18 to 30 to help with the campaign, an NYC official
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The NYC plans to recruit 120 volunteers specialized in different
fields, including 20 each for news reporting, computer
operations, international tourism promotion, and 50 to promote
Taiwan's campus life. Hopefuls are welcome to register through
April 14.
</P>
<P>
To enhance cultural and tourism exchanges between Taiwan and
Japan, the NYC is also going to solicit 10 international travel
volunteers to spur Japanese youths to visit Taiwan. To be
eligible, applicants must be Japanese nationals, reside in Taiwan
and speak both Chinese and Japanese language fluently, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Those interested in applying for travel volunteers are required
to possess experience in blog writing, Website management and
international cultural exchanges, the official added.
</P>
<P>
Those selected will be require to attend a training session
slated for April 27-28, after which they will be presented with
certificates by the NYC and begin to carry out volunteer
services.
</P>
<P>
Additionally, the NYC will grant them a certificate of service
and a free study tour around Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Application forms are available at the Website www.youthtravel.tw
</P>
